Course . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 138 The Danger from Enlargement . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 139 The Question of Wages . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 140 Chapter 23--Go Forth Into Many Places . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 142 The Need of Broader Plans . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 143 Build Up New Centers . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 146 A Failure to Appreciate God-Given Responsibilities . . . 147 Chapter 24--God's Purpose for His Institutions . . . . . . . . . 149 God's Purpose for the Sanitarium . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 151 The Value of A Study of God's Word . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 151 Contents v\n\nChapter 25--God's Purpose in Medical Missionary Work . 154 Educate Medical Missionaries . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 154 Our Work for Today . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 155 No Change in God's Cause . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 156 Words of Caution . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 156\n\nChapter 26--A Word of Caution . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 159 A Danger to Be Guarded Against . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 159 A High Standard . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 160 Teaching and Healing . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 161\n\nChapter 27--Uphold the Medical Work . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 162 The Need Of Caution . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 163 The Importance of Medical Missionary Work . . . . . . . . . 164 The Cause of Dearth in the Church . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 165 To Every Man His Work . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 166\n\nChapter 28--Unity of Effort . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 167 God's Building . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 168 A Templ